  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0bc0\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb4\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bc8 \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bc8 \u0b85\u0ba9\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b89\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The cabinet also approved the formation of a new constitutional select committee",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "Colombo political circles have confirmed that there are conditions for a resumption of efforts to draft a new constitution.",
        "It is said that permission has been granted to set up a Cabinet Select Committee for this purpose and the parties involved in the discussion have been informed by the Minister of Justice Dr. Wijatasa Rajapaksa.",
        "In recent days, Justice Minister Dr. Vijayadasa Rajapaksa has been accompanied by representatives of the Independent Action Group (RPF) and representatives of the United People's Power (UPFA) and the Tamil National Alliance (TNA) for discussions on the proposed 21st Amendment.",
        "Opposition groups called for a boycott of the 21st Amendment.",
        "At the time, it was said that the Minister of Justice had given his approval to set up a select committee for the new constitution.",
        "In this context, one of the delegates representing the Tamil National Alliance (TNA) suggested that the 21st Amendment could be scrapped and a new constitution could be drafted.",
        "However, there is a draft constitution proposed during the tenure of former President Chandrika Ammiyar as discussions are underway on whether it will be possible immediately. As well as various reports and proposals of the Constituent Assembly prepared during the last regime.",
        "Therefore, the representative of the federation stressed that there were no problems in drafting the new constitution immediately.",
        "However he acknowledged that their numbers were not enough to defeat Lukashenko's new constitution.",
        "At the same time, some parties are said to be ready to support the 21st Amendment if the new constitution is promised to be drafted within six months.",
        "It is noteworthy that despite requests for details from the Tamil National Alliance and the United People's Power regarding these discussions, the response was that the discussions on the form could not be disclosed as they were closed-door meetings."
      ],
